Description:

Mathematics Handbook for Science and Engineering is a comprehensive handbook for scientists, engineers, teachers and students at universities. 

The book presents in a lucid and accessible form classical areas of mathematics like algebra, geometry and analysis and also areas of current interest like discrete mathematics, probability, statistics, optimization and numerical analysis. 

It concentrates on definitions, results, formulas, graphs and tables and emphasizes concepts and methods with applications in technology and science. 

Includes over 450 graphs, figures and illustrations. There is an extensive, thoroughly cross-referenced index which lists over 1,400 terms.
